<br>
lvl 60 pali<br>
lvl 60 sk (w/epic)<br>
up to 3 lvl 54-60 monks (w/epic)<br>
60 shaman slowing<br>
54-58 enc tash<br>
<br>
In certain cases (Kael mainly) I can usually hold aggro by hugging the mob while all others stay just inside of melee range - but it's really not *me* taunting, it's a more the nature of the game mechanics, yet I still will have to chase the mob down off the enchanter and shaman in most cases after they've tash/malo/slowed, unless the sk or pali is holding aggro during that time.<br>
<br>
So anyway enough talk, basically looking for any suggestions on high taunt weapons - frostbringer is very nice, or would be if it wasn't cold-based, thus near worthless in most of SoV.  I plan on retaining that for offhand use simply due to its nice dmg/del ratio, but open to any other ideas.  Primarily after a good primary weapon - money is not much of an object,  nor is killing a mob that drops the weapon, just looking for advice and experience.<br>
<br>
